    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.7.0-dev+1446-g18152cf6f\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArchLinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkonsole 21.12.3\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nAUR\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. `nvim --clean`\r\n2. `:lua _G.on_cmdline_enter = function() vim.schedule(function() end) end`\r\n3. `:autocmd CmdlineEnter * lua _G.on_cmdline_enter()`\r\n4. `:lua vim.fn.input(\"Insert a really long text prompt that does not fit within a single line and thus causes the prompt to get wrapped around to the next line which triggers the bug with the first line of the input prompt being printed twice before the rest of the prompt\")`\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nPrompt shows normally with each line only appearing once\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nSome wrapped lines from the beginning appear twice and then the rest of the lines appear normally\r\n\r\n### Screenshot\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29580810/163254293-ec5c3d0a-d664-4c83-a847-817d49d314e3.png)\r\n",
