            "body": "The prompt gets printed twice:\r\n1. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/594ff34581907fed4956d4dc93c033dfdd5f7a69/src/nvim/ex_getln.c#L728-L735\r\n2. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/594ff34581907fed4956d4dc93c033dfdd5f7a69/src/nvim/ex_getln.c#L1196-L1198\r\n\r\nAnother way to reproduce the bug:\r\n```vim\r\nfunc P(h)\r\n  let p = ''\r\n  let j = 0\r\n  while j < a:h\r\n    let i = 0\r\n    let c = nr2char(char2nr('a') + j)\r\n    while i < &columns\r\n      let p = p .. c\r\n      let i = i + 1\r\n    endwhile\r\n    let j = j + 1\r\n  endwhile\r\n  return p\r\nendfunc\r\n\r\nfunc S(h)\r\n  lua vim.schedule(function() end)\r\n  call input(P(a:h))\r\nendfunc\r\n\r\nfunc E(h) \r\n  \"prints prompt error prompt\r\n  au CmdlineEnter * ++once echoerr 'whatever'\r\n  call input(P(a:h))\r\nendfunc\r\n\r\ncall S(4)\r\n\"call E(4)\r\n```",
